To the aspiring author wanting to work on more European focused stuff
I would've bothered you in thread but I was in Sjaelland for the weekend visiting family and going to visit some historical places to further ground Tribes, got some photos to represent the Eastern Coasts of Hathia for Spring Fever, and getting a tour of a Cold War Era Static Defenses which'll help me start drawing out how HSR defensive positions might be developed, among other things.

>Time Period
>Classical (i.e Rome, Greece, Germanic Tribes, and early Barbarian Kingdomes.)
>Early Medieval (Magyar Invasions, Vikings, Charlemagne, Investiture Controversy)
>High Medieval (Crusades, Black Death, Gothic Architecture, Mongols, Breaking of the Byzantines)
>Late Medieval (Hundred Years War, Fall of Granada, Italian Wars, Fall of Constantinople/Rise of the Turks, Anything before your pick of 1453 or 1492)
>Renaissance (From the last two dates to 1648 and the Westphalia, so Spanish and Turkish peaks, Rise of Russia, Reformation, the Long Wars (80 Years and 30 years Wars)
>Early Modern (From 1648 to 1756/63)
>Modern (from your pick of the last date until 1914)
>World Wars and Long Truce (1914-1949)
>Cold War (NATO, and the end of European international supremacy, when America was nice enough to rebuild this Continent)
>Modern Period From 1991-Now

And the second is where you want it to take place, and I'm sure you know where you have in mind.
